<title>USA: Standard Financial amends bylaws.</title>
<headline>Standard Financial amends bylaws.</headline>
<dateline>CHICAGO 1996-11-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Standard Financial Inc said Friday its board of directors approved a change in the company's bylaws to require 120 days' advance notice to nominate an individual for the board of directors, or to submit a proposal for consideration at the annual stockholders meeting.</p>
<p>Standard Financial did not say if the move was in response to any specific situations.</p>
<p>But in October, LaSalle/Kross Partners LP, a private investment fund, said it had purchased 5.2 percent of the bank holding company's outstanding shares.</p>
<p>Officials from both firms were not available for comment Friday.</p>
<p>--Reuters Chicago newsdesk, 312-408-8787</p>
